* {{audio|en-us-apology.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Etymology===
''Defense, justification'', from [[w:Vulgar Latin|Late Latin]] '''[[apologia]]''', from [[w:Ancient Greek|Greek]] '''[[apologia]]''' ''a speech in defense'', from '''[[apologeisthai]]''' ''to speak in one's defense'', from '''[[apologos]]''' ''an account, story'', from '''[[apo-]]''' ''from, off'' (see ''[[apo-]]'') + '''[[logos]]''' ''speech''.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|apologies}}

# What you say when you [[regret]] saying or doing something [[affect]]ing others.
# A formal [[justification]], [[defence]].

